    77	  exact rates the D0b n606 run recorded) and **fail-closed if a priced model lacks pinned pricing** (never
    78	  silently use a default). Carry the **D0b $10.7479** as the ledger's opening balance; the pre-call
    79	  **projected** cost (input+max-output tokens) must keep `ledger + projected ≤ $30` for BOTH reader and
    80	  distiller, checked **before** each call.
    81	- **Per-question cells — checkpoint or hard-stop (codex CONCERN):** load D0b's per-question
    82	  fathomdb+mem0 cells from `0.8.3-d0b-parity-v2.checkpoint.json`; if the checkpoint lacks per-question
    83	  records, **HARD-STOP and surface a paid-re-run decision** — never fall back to D0b aggregate class-means
    84	  (paired CIs against oracle require per-question cells).
    85	- **Cheap-validate FIRST** (`gemini-2.5-flash-lite`, class-balanced n≈40, ~$0.01): wire the 3 new arms +
    86	  the blind distiller + the rule; confirm a directional split before priced spend.
    87	- **Priced**: run **only** `oracle_raw`, `oracle_distilled`, `fathomdb_distilled` on the identical D0b
    88	  question ids ≈ **3×606 ≈ 1818 reader calls** (oracle contexts are SHORTER → cheaper/call). Est.
    89	  **~$6–10**; with the D0b $10.75 opening balance the projected total ≈ $17–21 < $30.
    90	- **Distiller — corpus-level, query-/answer-BLIND, capped (codex CONCERN Q4 + BLOCK Q5):** distill **every
    91	  candidate corpus doc ONCE** with a generic prompt (no query, no answers, no gold labels), persist
    92	  `{doc_id→distilled, prompt, model, hash}`, then **select** gold/retrieved ids from that frozen cache at
    93	  eval time (no label-selected distillation). Distiller = **local Qwen (OFFLINE-BUILD/$0)** or a
    94	  `--max-usd`-capped cheap model, **fail-closed** if unavailable. A test asserts the distiller call sees
    95	  neither `answers` nor `query`.
    96	- Resilient harness (atomic checkpoint, verified `--resume`, 429/5xx backoff, failure≠abstention,
    97	  completeness guard). Determinism: pinned hashes + temp 0/seed 0 + fixed bootstrap seed.
    98	
    99	## 5. Footprint
   100	EVAL-ONLY reader (the one approved priced seam) + OFFLINE-BUILD/$0-or-capped distiller. No in-library LLM,
   101	no engine/Rust change.
   102	
   103	## 6. TDD + outputs
   104	- RED: frozen `gap_decomposition_rule` truth-table (RETRIEVAL / FORM / MEM0_RESIDUAL / INCONCLUSIVE +
   105	  underpowered guard); oracle arms build the correct gold/distilled context (fixture catching wrong-doc /
   106	  empty / leaked-answer); **distiller blindness** (a test that the distiller call sees neither `query`
   107	  nor `answers`); paired bootstrap CI determinism; **`--max-usd` halts BEFORE the call that would exceed**.
   108	- GREEN: runner (extends `r2_parity_eval`); cheap-validate green end-to-end.
   109	- Outputs → `runs/0.8.3-gap-decomposition-n*.json` (per-class acc per arm; R/F/Resid + paired CIs + MDE;
   110	  the frozen verdict; $ ledger; confounds list; **per-arm answer-retention diagnostic** — fraction of questions whose distilled context still contains the gold answer string, reported SEPARATELY (a low-retention distilled arm is a lossy-distill artifact, NOT Mem0 superiority — codex v3)), `runs/0.8.3-gap-decomposition-report.md` (framed as
   111	  **bounded diagnostics**, with the explicit confounds from §1).
   112	
   113	## 7. The decision it informs (a lever DIRECTION, with caveats)
   114	- **RETRIEVAL_DOMINANT** (powered) ⇒ retrieval levers worth it → run 15b `--full` + Slice-20 PRF / D2.
   115	  Caveat: oracle strips distractors PRF/D2 can't, so this is the optimistic case — confirm the PRF lift
   116	  separately.
   117	- **DISTILLED_FORM_DOMINANT** (query-BLIND) ⇒ a short *query-blind distilled form* helps the reader → scope the Mem0-style
   118	  **memory-formation** experiment (offline distill/consolidate → index distilled units → re-measure);
   119	  PRF/D2 deprioritized. HITL footprint-scope decision (fork b).
   120	- **MEM0_RESIDUAL_DOMINANT** ⇒ Mem0's units add beyond distilled gold, but `Resid` bundles Mem0
