dev/plans/runs/0.8.3-slice-10-output.json:17:    "pipeline_works_evidence": "Cheap-validate (gemini-flash-lite, 8 q across all 4 memory classes, 3 arms = 24 calls, $0.0275, 0 errors, completeness 1.0): all arms ran, per-class recall + accuracy deltas + paired 95% CI + MDE produced, atomic checkpoint + auto-resume exercised, decide_083 emitted a mechanical verdict. Priced pilot (gpt-5.4, 12 q, 3 arms = 36 calls, $0.9693, 0 errors, completeness 1.0): the priced path works end-to-end + decide_083 emitted. Resume PROVEN before spend by a backend-free kill/restart unit test (test_resume_reuses_prior_cells_and_recalls_only_absent: re-calls ONLY the 16 absent cells, zero re-spend on the 48 reused; failure!=abstention; completeness guard rejects an incomplete matrix). 12/12 d0b unit tests + 30 (-k d0b/parity/resume/decide_083/mem0) green.",
dev/plans/runs/0.8.3-slice-10-output.json:19:      "artifact": "dev/plans/runs/0.8.3-d0b-cheapval.json",
dev/plans/runs/0.8.3-slice-10-output.json:29:      "note": "pipeline-proof on a tiny subset; NOT the citable per-class parity verdict (that is Phase B at N=606). cheapval accuracy fathomdb-mem0 deltas were 0.0 (both arms equal on the 8-q toy subset); recall deltas were non-vacuous (knowledge_update +0.5, temporal +0.5)."
dev/plans/runs/0.8.3-slice-10-output.json:32:    "cost_per_question_usd": 0.026925,
dev/plans/runs/0.8.3-slice-10-output.json:33:    "cost_per_question_note": "per (question x arm) answerer call (the prompt's 'cost/question x (606 q x n_priced_arms)' factor). per-question across all 3 arms = $0.080775. Input-token-dominated: ~21,484 prompt tokens/call (long LME multi-turn session bodies in context); ~14 completion tokens. gpt-5.4 priced at the documented _DEFAULT_PRICE (1.25/5.00 per 1M) — gpt-5.4 is not in the explicit price table.",
dev/plans/runs/0.8.3-slice-10-output.json:36:    "within_20_budget": false,
dev/plans/runs/0.8.3-slice-10-output.json:37:    "within_20_budget_detail": "NOT <= $20 at the pilot config (~$48.95; also exceeds the aggregate $30 program budget on D0b alone). $0 cost-reduction levers (analytic, via project_full_cost): context-budget <= ~32k chars (~8k tok) -> ~$18.44 (<=20); context <= 24k chars -> ~$13.90; k=4 full-body -> ~$19.74 (<=20); k=3 -> ~$14.87. The window-fit lever is applied identically across arms (R2 invariant preserved); reducing context may lower identical-answerer accuracy (a measurement-validity tradeoff for the HITL). Phase B is BLOCKED until the orchestrator/HITL authorizes a reduced-context config or raises the budget.",
dev/plans/runs/0.8.3-slice-10-output.json:38:    "mem0_status": "STOOD UP. Installed mem0ai 2.0.7 + chromadb + sentence-transformers into an ISOLATED env (--target /tmp/d0b-mem0-env on PYTHONPATH; canonical .venv NOT polluted). try_build() -> build_local_mem0_config (airlock qwen3.6-27b LLM + local bge-small embedder + on-disk chroma, per-run isolated; NO Mem0 cloud) constructs a working adapter that ingested + retrieved live in both cheap-validate and pilot. Mem0OSSAdapter.retrieve made version-robust to the mem0 2.x search API (filters={'user_id'} + top_k + threshold) via signature introspection; the <=1.x fake-backend conformance test still passes.",
dev/plans/runs/0.8.3-slice-10-output.json:39:    "graphiti_status": "CLEAN BLOCKER (not run). No local Neo4j/FalkorDB graph backend is running (neo4j 7474 down, falkor/redis 6379 down) and graphiti_core is not installed. Standing up Graphiti/Zep needs a graph-DB server + graphiti_core + a per-doc-LLM-extraction adapter behind the R2 contract (its own ingest cost, like Mem0). Per design 0.8.3-mem0-parity.md §3, Graphiti/Zep is the SECOND comparator, NOT a blocker on the Mem0 resolution; the gap runs with {Mem0, naive-RAG}. Phase-B recipe: docker run falkordb/falkordb (or neo4j), pip install graphiti-core into the isolated env, add eval/graphiti_local.build_graphiti_adapter behind the retrieve(question,k)->[Hit] contract (build_live_adapters already imports it lazily and records a clean blocker when absent).",
dev/plans/runs/0.8.3-slice-10-output.json:44:      "explanation": "decide_083 was fed the cheap-validate accuracy fathomdb-mem0 deltas + eu7_recall=0.896 (the honest current eu7 point estimate per design §5) + latency_ok=true. The eu7 hard-gate (floor 0.90) fires first and correctly returns NOT_REACHED blocked_by='eu7'. This is the correct mechanical output, not the parity gap. At Phase B with the real N=150 per class, expect NOT_REACHED underpowered:<class> (manifest implied-N proxy: every class needs N>>150 for paired MDE<=eps=0.05) once eu7 clears — the per-class gap numbers still LAND (design §5) and the under-power triggers a HITL escalation (grow N vs accept), not suppression."
dev/plans/runs/0.8.3-slice-10-output.json:47:      {"id": "phase-b-cost-exceeds-20-budget", "severity": "HITL/orchestrator decision", "detail": "Projected full priced D0b ~$48.95 > $20 at the pilot config. Authorize a window-fit context budget (<= ~32k chars -> ~$18) or k<=4 (~$20), OR raise the budget. Reduced context may lower identical-answerer accuracy (validity tradeoff)."},
dev/plans/runs/0.8.3-slice-10-output.json:49:      {"id": "power-underpowered-HITL", "severity": "HITL-escalation (expected, Phase B)", "detail": "N_min=150 per class is expected to remain under-powered for a strict paired MDE<=eps=0.05 parity claim (implied N: factoid 524, knowledge_update 601, multi_session 768, temporal 752). Run the real paired power-check in Phase B and escalate to HITL on any mde>eps; report the gap regardless."},
