dev/plans/runs/F0-review-20260504T121732Z.md:5767:112 "details": "Two integration tests cover this. (a) reader_workers_exit_on_close_and_drop_connections: opens engine, fires 32 dummy searches (each errors on empty query, but exercises the dispatch/return path), calls Engine::close, then asserts live_reader_worker_count_for_test()==0 within a 2 s deadline and that subsequent search() surfaces a closing/storage error rather than hanging. (b) reader_workers_exit_on_drop_without_explicit_close: opens engine, drops it without close(); ReaderWorkerPool::Drop is invoked synchronously, which sends Shutdown to each worker and joins every JoinHandle; the closing scope returning at all is the assertion. Both tests pass in 0.12 s combined."
